Assore jumped 10.6% to R228 South32 6.5% to R29.28 and Kumba 6% to R159.20 as the miners tracked the spot price of iron ore which rebounded to levels last seen in January 2015.Kumba s parent Anglo American rose 4.6% to R207.23 while South32 s former parent BHP Billiton rose 3.5% to R230.42.In Sydney BHP closed 8.24% higher at A$24.42.Trump s pledge to invest $500bn in fixing the US s crumbling infrastructure nearly twice what Hillary Clinton said she would spend saw copper gain 3.4% to $5 414/tonne on the London Metal Exchange on Thursday morning.- TMG Digital/BusinessLIVE